cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "F(AI)²R: FAIR Research with AI in the Loop, Twice"
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Krebs"
    given-names: "Florian"
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6033-801X"
    affiliation: "DLR Zentrum für Leichtbauproduktionstechnologie (ZLP), Augsburg, Germany"
    email: "florian.krebs@dlr.de"
abstract: >-
  F(AI)²R extends the FAIR principles (Findable, Accessible,
  Interoperable, Reusable) for scholarly artefacts produced with the
  active participation of Large Language Models. The (AI) factor is
  multiplied through every FAIR axis, squared because each axis demands
  two passes over every artefact: an authoring pass and an audit pass.
  The contribution is the integration of eight individually unoriginal
  practices into a single discipline, enforced by a ten-stage agent
  pipeline. Released as a worked example with prompts, build pipeline,
  PROV-O graph, and public site.
keywords:
  - FAIR
  - PROV-O
  - reproducibility
  - LLM
  - scholarly communication
  - provenance
  - research data management
  - HMC
  - NFDI4Ing
